# game-data-models

## Core Game Entities

### Card System
- Card type hierarchy with distinct rules:
  - Heroes (1 per deck limit)
  - Units (combat stats + initiative)
  - Actions (instant effects)
  - Structures (zone-based persistence)

### Battlefield Grid
- Specialized zones:
  - Player frontline/backline 
  - Neutral territory
  - Movement/positioning restrictions
  - Zone control mechanics

### Player Resources
- Multi-resource management:
  - Energy (capped at 10, +1 per turn)
  - Momentum (0-5, gained through combat)
  - Health (starting at 20)

### Faction Mechanics
- Seven unique faction implementations:
  - Solaris: Energy manipulation, predictive algorithms
  - Umbral: Stealth, information warfare
  - Neuralis: Mind control, mental projection
  - Aeonic: Time manipulation
  - Infernal: Blood sacrifice mechanics
  - Primordial: Evolution acceleration
  - Synthetic: System optimization

### Combat Resolution
- Initiative-based attack order
- Simultaneous damage resolution
- Special combat keywords:
  - Quick Attack
  - Overwhelm
  - Lifesteal
  - Shield

### Game State Model
- Turn phases:
  - Draw Phase
  - Energy Phase (resource generation)
  - Main Phase (card playing)
  - Combat Phase
  - End Phase
- State transitions with validation rules
- Crisis event triggers and effects

